T|19 ·|0|The lab for the im-generation ag, Leonardo: every generated im in one place to view, download and reuse, plus br kits (colors, logos, assets) per workspace.
T|19 ·|1|
T|Purp|0|"The lab for my im generation md." A gallery + workbench where the owner can see everything Leonardo has created, reuse/download assets, and define br kits (color schemes, logos, assets) for each workspace so generated imagery stays on-br.
T|Purp|1|
T|Page|0|Title: Asset Lab, breadcrumb Vibe w/ AI / Asset Lab · Leonardo.
T|Page|1|Sub-line: "Leonardo is rendering X concepts · 1,2XX assets saved across your brands."
T|Page|2|Top-right toggles: Gallery, gn, Thumbnails (modes/views).
T|Page|3|Spend tracker — cost figures for im generation, e.g. $0.18 / $7.42 / $128.60 (last render / today / month), w/ a monthly budget note (e.g. "$129 / $200").
T|Page|4|
T|Filt|0|Search assets ("neon thumbnail," "human that flat lay," "Maria hero," …).
T|Filt|1|br filter chips: All brands, Vibe, By ds, Valhalla, etc.
T|Filt|2|tp filter chips: All tp, Thumbnail, Post, Hero, Cinematic, Graphic, etc.
T|Filt|3|
T|Asse|0|A masonry/grid of generated images, each tile showing the visual plus metadata: title (e.g. "Long-form thumb · big face, less text," "Cinematic Site hero — Maria project · cinematic dusk skyline," "The 5-asset stack"), the br/workspace, tp, a cost (e.g. $1.7/$1.2), and a relative time.
T|Asse|1|Tile actions: download, reuse, and inspect what Leonardo was working w/.
T|Asse|2|
T|Bran|0|br Kit panel scoped to a workspace ("All brands" / per-br):
T|Bran|1|Display / style settings (e.g. "Space Mood").
T|Bran|2|Ratio presets.
T|Bran|3|Personas / br persona assets (e.g. "Nina · br persona") used to keep generated humans consistent.
T|Bran|4|Colors, logos, assets for each workspace's br identity.
T|Bran|5|
T|Agen|0|Leonardo is the im-generation ag; outputs here feed sl Approvals (the 8 candidate images per post), YouTube Studio (thumbnails), Cinematic Sites (hero imagery), etc.
T|Agen|1|Cost/budget tracking is built in so im-gen spend stays controlled.